## File Organization

```
app/           → Pages and API routes (App Router)
components/    → React components
lib/           → Utilities, constants, validation
data/          → Static content data
public/images/ → Static images
styles/        → Global CSS
types/         → TypeScript definitions
```

## Import Aliases

Use the `@/` alias for absolute imports:

```tsx
import { Component } from '@/components/Component'
import { CONSTANT } from '@/lib/constants'
import { CaseStudy } from '@/types'
```

## TypeScript

- Always define explicit types for props and return values
- Use interfaces for object shapes
- Avoid `any` - use `unknown` if type is truly unknown
- Export types from `types/index.ts`

```tsx
// Good
interface Props {
  title: string
  onClick: () => void
}

// Bad
const Component = (props: any) => ...
```

## Environment Variables

- Access via `process.env.VARIABLE_NAME`
- Client-side vars must be prefixed with `NEXT_PUBLIC_`
- Never commit real values - use `.env.example` as template
- Validate required vars in `lib/env-validation.ts`

## Security Checklist

- [ ] Rate limit public API endpoints
- [ ] Validate all user inputs
- [ ] Escape HTML in user-provided content
- [ ] Never expose internal errors
- [ ] Use HTTPS in production

## Performance

- Use `next/image` for optimized images
- Add `priority` to above-fold images
- Use passive event listeners
- Lazy load below-fold components
- Check bundle size before adding dependencies

## Next.js Best Practices (from cursor.directory patterns)

### Server vs Client Components
- Default to Server Components (no directive needed)
- Add `'use client'` only for: hooks, event handlers, browser APIs
- Keep client components small and leaf-level

### Data Fetching
- Fetch data in Server Components when possible
- Use `loading.tsx` for streaming/suspense
- Use `error.tsx` for error boundaries

### Routing
- Use App Router conventions: `page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `loading.tsx`
- Dynamic routes: `[slug]/page.tsx`
- Route groups: `(group)/page.tsx` for organization without URL impact

### Metadata
```tsx
// Static metadata
export const metadata: Metadata = {
  title: 'Page Title | Raúl Mermans',
  description: 'Page description for SEO',
}

// Dynamic metadata
export async function generateMetadata({ params }): Promise<Metadata> {
  return { title: `${params.slug} | Raúl Mermans` }
}
```

## Session Continuity

Use `SESSION.md` to maintain context across coding sessions:
- **Start**: Read SESSION.md for current state, check TASKS.md
- **End**: Update status, add session entry, note next steps

## Git Workflow

Use atomic commits with conventional prefixes:

```
<type>(<scope>): <description>
```

| Prefix | Use For |
|--------|---------|
| `feat` | New features |
| `fix` | Bug fixes |
| `docs` | Documentation |
| `style` | Formatting/CSS |
| `refactor` | Code restructuring |
| `perf` | Performance |
| `chore` | Maintenance |

**Example:** `feat(case-study): add remoria gallery section`

**Before committing:**
- Run `npm run lint`
- Run `npm run type-check`
- Don't commit `.env` files
